apwsE9511250054-2-2-1 The Athens Geodynamic Institute reported that the temblor struck at 11.47 am (0847 GMT) in the vicinity of the town of Kozani, about 300 kilometers (180 miles) northwest of the capital. 
apwsE9511250054-2-2-1 Aftershocks continued to rock the region through the day. 
apwsE9511250054-2-2-1 The quake was felt in cities as far apart as Athens in the south and Salonica in the north, where an old warehouse collapsed. 
apwsE9511250054-2-2-1 Army troops and teams of government workers went into the affected areas to help people whose houses were destroyed or damaged. 
apwsE9511250054-2-2-1 Authorities advised residents to stay out of houses that had suffered any damages, in case of another strong quake. 
apwsE9511250054-2-2-1 A spokesman at the Public Order Ministry in Athens said that 16 people were treated briefly in hospitals for slight injuries, most of them caused by panic. 
apwsE9511250054-2-2-1 He said that 190 old houses collapsed in villages in Grevena province, while another 60 were damaged. 
apwsE9511250054-2-2-1 In the vicinity of Kozani 50 houses and three village bell towers collapsed, while another 20 houses suffered cracks and a bridge on a secondary road was damaged. 
apwsE9511250054-2-2-1 There were also cracks in buildings in the towns of Florina and Trikala, he said. 
